<br><br>
<div class="text">
<b>The Hunter</b>, also known as “Patient Zero”, is an enigmatic entity that can be found within the depths of Level 14. It is one of the only entities that resides in Level 14 and its main objective is to hunt down any wanderers who enter the level.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.25s;">
The entity's skin is moist and completely pitch black, shrouded in some sort of darkness that seems to absorb all sources of light. Its form is amorphous, with numerous writhing, octopus-like tentacles that extend in all directions, seemingly acting as the entity's "arms". These tentacles possess powerful flexibility and intelligence, capable of fast and precise movements.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.75s;">
On each of <b>The Hunter</b>'s tentacles, there are small openings that resemble mouths with sharp, dangerous teeth. From the openings, <b>The Hunter</b> can release small leech-like entities, also known as "Infecting Agents". These "Infecting Agents" are all under <b>The Hunter</b>'s control, and any command <b>The Hunter</b> gives, they will follow without any thought or consideration.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.25s;">
The Infecting Agents are small, worm-like creatures that squirm along the ground extremely swiftly. They possess a mouth that is filled with rows of sharp, razor teeth. Their mouths also possess the ability to spit out radioactive substances. The substances can vary, ranging from corrosive acids to life-ending toxins, to capture its prey.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.75s;">
When <b>The Hunter</b> is nearby, wanderers will suddenly feel a sense of dread. The temperature will drop drastically and the air will become heavy with a thick, smoky aura. The very atmosphere of the level will be poisoned when <b>The Hunter</b> is nearby.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 2.25s;">
If you sense <b>The Hunter</b> is nearby, get out of the room immediately and run. Once you make eye contact with <b>The Hunter</b>, there is no hope of saving you.
</div>
